Makes: 7 x 400g jarsIngredients:4kg yellow cling peaches, washed, peeled and chopped into blocks (start off with about 5kg of fruit)375ml (1 cups) waterFinely grated rind of 2-3 lemon100ml fresh lemon juice4 sticks of cinnamon2.5kg sugar, warmed in the ovenMethod:1) Place 2 saucers of water in the fridge, this is to test for setting point later.2) In a large preserving pan combine the peaches, water, lemon rind, juice and cinnamon sticks. Bring to the boil and boil till the peaches are tender. To test for readiness, use a toothpick or matchstick to pierce the fruit; if you can pierce it easily, it's ready.3) Add the warmed sugar to the fruit and over a medium heat stir till the sugar has dissolved. Stop stirring, increase the heat and skim the scum off the surface with a slotted spoon. Boil till setting point is reached. To test for setting point, remove a saucer of water from the fridge and add a spoonful of jam. It if holds it's shape and you can run your finger through the mixture and it leaves a trail, it is ready. If not, continue boiling and test again. The mixture should have a syrupy golden look. 4) Pour the hot jam into the sterilised* jars and fill to the brim. Seal while still warm.1) Preheat the oven to 100 C. 2) Wash the jars in hot soapy water and rinse well. 3) Place in the oven and heat for 30 minutes. Remove and place on a wooden board. 4) Place the lids in a pan and cover with water. Bring to the boil and boil for 10 minutes.